cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper focuses on improving depth estimation from monocular videos by exploiting temporal information. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel spatial-temporal CLSTM structure and applies generative adversarial learning, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the real-time performance of their approach, which suggests it could fall under cs.RO (Robotics and Control) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
